# Cursor Prompt — kassythreads Luxury Beauty Booking Site

---

## Project Identity

You are building **kassythreads** — a luxury hair removal and eyebrow threading studio with lash-lift services. The target audience is women aged 22–45 who value precision beauty work and expect a premium digital experience. The site must feel like a high-end spa brand, not a generic booking widget. The reference aesthetic is https://poshbrowspro.com/ — editorial, cinematic, social-proof-driven — but more refined and owned end-to-end.

The site is **not a brochure with a Booksy link**. It is a fully owned booking platform. Booksy is being replaced entirely. Every design and engineering decision should reflect that this is the client's permanent digital home — not a placeholder.

---

## Stack

```
apps/
├── web/          # Next.js 15 App Router (RSC-first)
└── api/          # Express + Mikro-ORM + PostgreSQL

Infrastructure (Docker Compose profiles: local | prod):
  postgres        # PostgreSQL 16
  minio           # Object storage (videos, images, assets)
  imgproxy        # On-the-fly image optimization (WebP, resize, crop)
  ntfy            # Push notifications
  caddy           # Reverse proxy + auto SSL (prod only)
```

**Frontend decisions:**
- Next.js 15 App Router — RSC for all static/marketing surfaces, `'use client'` only where interactivity is required
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Framer Motion — scroll-triggered entrance animations, slow luxury cubic-bezier curves
- Embla Carousel — service cards, testimonials, before/after gallery
- `react-compare-slider` — before/after treatment reveals
- Custom imgproxy loader for `next/image`
- No `react-slick`, no jQuery-based carousel libraries

**Backend decisions:**
- Express REST API at `/api/*`
- Mikro-ORM with PostgreSQL — single ORM, single migration system
- MinIO for all media (videos, images, before/after photos)
- imgproxy sidecar for image transforms
- Resend for transactional email
- Stripe for deposits and payments

