## Design System

### Palette
```
--color-bg:        #0a0a08    /* near-black warm */
--color-surface:   #111110    /* card/section backgrounds */
--color-border:    #1e1e1c    /* subtle dividers */
--color-gold:      #c9a96e    /* primary accent — warm gold, not yellow */
--color-gold-muted:#8a7050    /* secondary gold for borders, icons */
--color-cream:     #f5f0e8    /* primary text on dark */
--color-muted:     #7a7570    /* subtext, captions */
--color-white:     #ffffff    /* high-contrast moments only */
```

### Typography
```
Display:  "Cormorant Garamond" — weight 300–400, tracked wide, uppercase for labels
Body:     "DM Sans" — weight 300–400, generous line-height (1.7)
Utility:  "DM Mono" — prices, booking times, status indicators
```

Load via `next/font/google`. Never use system fonts on public-facing surfaces.

### Motion Signature
All entrance animations use this cubic-bezier — it feels unhurried and expensive:
```ts
const LUXURY_EASE = [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]
const LUXURY_DURATION = 0.85

// Standard entrance
{ opacity: 0, y: 32 } → { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { duration: LUXURY_DURATION, ease: LUXURY_EASE } }

// Stagger children (service cards, gallery items)
staggerChildren: 0.1

// Always use whileInView + viewport={{ once: true }}
// Never animate on every scroll pass
```

Never use spring physics or bounce easing on a luxury brand. Never use `ease-in-out` — it reads generic.

### Image Optimization
All images served through imgproxy. Use the custom loader:

```ts
// lib/imgproxy-loader.ts
export default function imgproxyLoader({ src, width, quality }: { src: string; width: number; quality?: number }) {
  const base = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_IMGPROXY_URL
  return `${base}/rs:fill:${width}/q:${quality ?? 82}/plain/${src}@webp`
}
```

Register in `next.config.ts`:
```ts
images: {
  loader: 'custom',
  loaderFile: './src/lib/imgproxy-loader.ts',
}
```

