## Priority Components — Build These First

### 1. VideoHero (server component)

**Reference:** The Posh Brows homepage opens with a full-viewport muted autoplay video loop showing hands performing threading/lash work in close-up. The effect is cinematic and immediate.

**Requirements:**
- Full viewport height (`100svh` — use `svh` not `vh` for mobile Safari)
- Muted, autoplay, loop, playsInline — all four attributes required
- `preload="metadata"` — do not block page load with video download
- `poster` attribute pointing to a WebP still from imgproxy (first frame of the video)
- Video stored in MinIO, referenced via env var `NEXT_PUBLIC_MINIO_URL`
- Dark gradient overlay: `linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(10,10,8,0.2) 0%, rgba(10,10,8,0.6) 60%, rgba(10,10,8,0.95) 100%)`
- Headline: Cormorant Garamond, 300 weight, ~80px desktop / 48px mobile, centered, cream, tracked `0.15em`
- Subhead: DM Sans, 300 weight, ~16px, muted color, tracked `0.3em`, uppercase
- CTA: ghost button with 1px gold border, cream text, no fill — hover fills with gold at 10% opacity
- Scrolling marquee below the fold break: alternating "THREADING · LASH LIFT · BROW DESIGN ·" in DM Mono, gold color, 12px
- Mobile: video plays on iOS (playsInline is critical), headline drops to 42px, CTA is full-width

```tsx
// Approximate structure
export default function VideoHero() {
  return (
    <section style={{ position: 'relative', height: '100svh', overflow: 'hidden' }}>
      <video
        autoPlay muted loop playsInline
        preload="metadata"
        poster={`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_IMGPROXY_URL}/rs:fill:1920:1080/plain/${HERO_VIDEO_POSTER}@webp`}
        style={{ position: 'absolute', inset: 0, width: '100%', height: '100%', objectFit: 'cover' }}
      >
        <source src={`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_MINIO_URL}/videos/hero.mp4`} type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <div className="overlay"> {/* gradient + content */} </div>
    </section>
  )
}
```

**Performance rules:**
- Video file must be under 8MB (H.264, CRF 28, 1080p max) — add a comment in the component noting this constraint
- Do not autoplay on `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` — respect this media query
- Poster image must load before video — it is the first visual impression

