### 2. GifProductSection (server component)

**Reference:** Posh Brows uses a 3-panel section with animated GIFs showing products in use — each GIF has a caption and a shop/learn CTA. This is the section immediately below the hero. It drives conversion on specific services.

**Requirements:**
- 3-column grid on desktop, stacked on mobile
- Each panel: full-bleed GIF/video loop (treat short MP4 loops the same as GIFs — use `<video>` with no controls, autoplay, muted, loop, playsInline)
- Panels stored in MinIO: `NEXT_PUBLIC_MINIO_URL/content/service-{slug}.mp4`
- Dark semi-transparent overlay on each panel with service name and CTA
- On hover: overlay fades slightly, a thin gold border appears on the panel
- Service name: Cormorant Garamond, 400 weight, 28px, cream
- CTA link: DM Sans, 300, 12px, gold, tracked `0.2em`, uppercase, underline on hover
- Section background: `--color-surface`
- Data driven — panels come from an API fetch to `/api/services/featured` at build time (RSC fetch)

```tsx
// Approximate structure
const services = await fetch(`${process.env.API_URL}/api/services/featured`).then(r => r.json())

return (
  <section className="gif-product-section">
    <div className="grid">
      {services.map(service => (
        <GifPanel key={service.id} service={service} />
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>
)
```

