## General Engineering Rules

### RSC Boundary Rules
- `VideoHero`, `ServicesGrid`, `GifProductSection`, `SocialWall` — server components, no `'use client'`
- `BookingFlow`, `EmblaCarousel`, `BeforeAfterSlider`, `MobileMenu` — client components
- `UGCGallery` shell is client (hover interactions), but data is fetched in RSC parent and passed as props
- Never fetch data inside a client component if it can be fetched in an RSC parent

### Tailwind Rules
- Use CSS variables from the design system as Tailwind theme extensions — do not hardcode hex values in className strings
- `100svh` not `100vh` everywhere height: screen is used
- `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` respected on all animations

### Framer Motion Rules
- All public-facing animations: `whileInView` + `viewport={{ once: true }}`
- Easing: always `LUXURY_EASE = [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]`, never spring, never bounce
- Wrap Framer Motion components in a `'use client'` wrapper — never import motion in a server component directly

```tsx
// components/client/AnimatedSection.tsx
'use client'
import { motion } from 'framer-motion'
export const LUXURY_EASE = [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]
export { motion }
```

### Embla Carousel Rules
- Use `embla-carousel-react` with `embla-carousel-autoplay` plugin
- Autoplay config: `{ delay: 5000, stopOnInteraction: true }`
- Loop: true, align: 'start'
- Never use react-slick, Swiper, or any carousel with a jQuery dependency
- Custom prev/next buttons — never use Embla's default arrows (they are not luxury)

### Video Rules
Every video element on the site must have: `autoPlay muted loop playsInline preload="metadata"`
Missing any of these breaks iOS Safari autoplay. This is non-negotiable.

### MinIO Asset Convention
```
videos/hero.mp4                    # Hero video
videos/hero-poster.jpg             # Hero poster still
content/service-{slug}.mp4        # GIF product section panels
gallery/before-after/{id}.jpg      # Before/after gallery
instagram/cache/{instagram_id}.jpg # Cached Instagram thumbnails
```

### API Conventions
```
GET  /api/services/featured        # 3 featured services for GifProductSection
GET  /api/services                 # All services for ServicesGrid
GET  /api/instagram/feed           # Cached Instagram posts (approved=true)
GET  /api/availability             # Available slots (booking flow)
POST /api/bookings                 # Create booking
POST /api/stripe/checkout          # Stripe deposit session
```

